<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="656" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[804,1397,1021,1448]" lastBlockId="37.[186,1394,1454,2275]" pageId="37" pageNumber="656">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[804,1069,1257,1290]" pageId="37" pageNumber="656">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity box="[1277,1387,1257,1290]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="37" pageNumber="656" unit="mm" value="66.0">66 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity box="[863,966,1300,1329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="37" pageNumber="656" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
, ear 
<quantity box="[1047,1149,1300,1329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="37" pageNumber="656" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
, hindfoot 
<quantity box="[1309,1393,1300,1329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="656" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
(all details from male holotype), forearm 32-35 mm. Fur is short and sparse, covering rump but not extending onto uropatagium, dark sepia-brown above with no grizzling or spots, pale brown to dark beige below becoming paler mid-ventrally but with no mid-ventral markings or contrasting ventral flank-stripe. Upper lip has five well-defined wrinkles on each side and many spoon-hairs. Wings and uropatagium are blackish brown. Ears are blackish brown and relatively short (extending halfway along muzzle when laid flat), inner margins connected by interaural band of skin having knob-like protuberance and backward-facing pocket but no interaural crest. Tragusis small, subrectangular, and concealed by antitragus which is large and roughly rectangular. Anterior palate is narrowly emarginated, and basisphenoid pits are moderately deep. As is typical for 
<taxonomicName box="[190,261,1809,1842]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Mops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="656" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mops</taxonomicName>
, cusps on M? have third ridge much reduced. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 48 and FNa = 54.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
